@quartzmo I'm having a hard time seeing exactly where this is happening as well, but it looks like somewhere in the execute/retry code this is happening.

But one thing that occurred to me is I don't think I'm looking at the correct branch. Is the datastore code in https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-ruby? On the master, or 0.12 branch?

Also I think it is happening in the LookupResponse decoding, but since this looks like a generic type, is there a way we might be able to get an example of the expected entity?

@bmclean Thanks! I was questioning reality there for a moment!

@apolcyn Not `master`. It looks to me from the backtraces that both @timanovsky and @bmclean  are using `0.12.1`. So if you have cloned the repo, use:

```
$ git checkout v0.12.1
$ bundle install
```
